=E2=80=99s mostly about Alameda. Those topics are, of course, related: The =
problem at FTX, in Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s story and also really in the oth=
er story, is that it loaned a lot of money to Alameda and Alameda lost it. =
So you might ask questions like =E2=80=9Cwhy on earth did FTX loan Alameda =
all that money,=E2=80=9D and again the two possible answers would be (1) be=
cause FTX thought it was a good idea at the time and (2) to steal it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So here Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s goal is to arg=
ue that lending money to Alameda was rational. The basic form of the argume=
